Vol / Page: 84
Edition:
Quote: It was a pity Taumarunui was dry. She could do with a few spots herself to take away the taste of these last two weeks. 1978 editorial note 189 `spots'. Any alcoholic drinks, but usually spirits. The verbal forms `to spot' and `spotting' were common.
